109const char* CodecTypeToPayloadString(VideoCodecType type) {
110 switch (type) {
111 case kVideoCodecVP8:
112 return kPayloadNameVp8;
113 case kVideoCodecVP9:
114 return kPayloadNameVp9;
115 case kVideoCodecAV1:
116 return kPayloadNameAv1;
117 case kVideoCodecH264:
118 return kPayloadNameH264;
119#ifndef DISABLE_H265
120 case kVideoCodecH265:
121 return kPayloadNameH265;
122#endif
123 case kVideoCodecMultiplex:
124 return kPayloadNameMultiplex;
125 case kVideoCodecGeneric:
126 return kPayloadNameGeneric;
127 }
128 RTC_CHECK_NOTREACHED();
129}

131VideoCodecType PayloadStringToCodecType(const std::string& name) {
132 if (absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(name, kPayloadNameVp8))
133 return kVideoCodecVP8;
134 if (absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(name, kPayloadNameVp9))
135 return kVideoCodecVP9;
136 if (absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(name, kPayloadNameAv1))
137 return kVideoCodecAV1;
138 if (absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(name, kPayloadNameH264))
139 return kVideoCodecH264;
140#ifndef DISABLE_H265
141 if (absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(name, kPayloadNameH265))
142 return kVideoCodecH265;
143#endif
144 if (absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(name, kPayloadNameMultiplex))
145 return kVideoCodecMultiplex;
146 return kVideoCodecGeneric;
147}
